<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1352297-when-theseus-finds-ariadne-passed-out">When Theseus finds Ariadne passed out after the ritual on Naxos, what does she have in her hand that makes Theseus sick? 

I assumed it was the fawn&#39;s heart (Theseus saw the mangled corpse in the forest), but I don&#39;t believe it is properly explained?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1352297'><a id="like_count_community_question_1352297" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/1352297?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">2 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F93941.The_King_Must_Die">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1352297-when-theseus-finds-ariadne-passed-out">3 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1352297-when-theseus-finds-ariadne-passed-out">See all 4 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/4897096-j-andrew-brantley"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1458515847i/4897096._UY100_CR25,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/4897096-j-andrew-brantley">J. Andrew Brantley</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    Ariadne had the heart of the newly crowned King of Naxos, who was sacrificed at the feast of Dionysus. In some versions of Greek mythology, the Titans<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    Ariadne had the heart of the newly crowned King of Naxos, who was sacrificed at the feast of Dionysus. In some versions of Greek mythology, the Titans kill and dismember Dionysus. Athena retrieves his heart and gives it to Zeus. He is able to regenerate Dionysus from Semele via the heart. So the Dionysian priestesses of Naxos would rip out their King's heart, to bring about the reincarnation of the Dionysus. That is why Theseus is so repulsed and horrified by Ariadne, she claimed to come from such an "advanced" society (she would refer to him as her "barbarian"), yet could do something utterly inhumane. <a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</span>
</div>
</div>
