<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/50235607-susan-marcus"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1450813496i/50235607._UY100_CR6,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/50235607-susan-marcus">Susan Marcus</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I was surprised but not disappointed, As I read the work, I was wondering about Asterion&apos;s role as well as the different introduction and use of Ariad<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I was surprised but not disappointed, As I read the work, I was wondering about Asterion's role as well as the different introduction and use of Ariadne's thread. The ending made sense. What disturbed me was Renault's depiction of Asterion as a 'dark' man, obese, squat, and rapacious. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
