<div id="review_1455835420" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1455835420" />
    <a title="Agnieszka" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/704067-agnieszka"><img alt="Agnieszka" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1354899202p2/704067.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1455835420?book_show_action=true">Nov 30, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Agnieszka" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Agnieszka" href="/user/show/704067-agnieszka">Agnieszka</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/704067-agnieszka?shelf=women-writers">women-writers</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1455835420" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1344338468521255806">It&apos;s historical fiction based on myth and also history, which means it&apos;s basically an amazing fantasy story. Theseus, founder-hero of Athens has amazing adventures. There&apos;s battle, ancient kingdoms, magic, ancient rites, messages from gods, incredible heroism, pride and honor, tragedy, wonder. And it&apos;s all from the point of view of Theseus, whose Ancient Greek way of thinking is different enough from our own that you might as well be reading science fiction. It is so, so good.</span>
  <span id="freeText1344338468521255806" style="display:none">It's historical fiction based on myth and also history, which means it's basically an amazing fantasy story. Theseus, founder-hero of Athens has amazing adventures. There's battle, ancient kingdoms, magic, ancient rites, messages from gods, incredible heroism, pride and honor, tragedy, wonder. And it's all from the point of view of Theseus, whose Ancient Greek way of thinking is different enough from our own that you might as well be reading science fiction. It is so, so good.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1344338468521255806" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
